about 50 or so people on taiwan will not object to being called zhōngguó rén but there is a significant portion of the population around 40 on taiwan who will be offended by the term
although there are some correlations between these self descriptions to ethnic characteristics they largely reflect the individual s political belief in the question of taiwan s political status
